---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About: Chulbuji + Meta-Chulbuji"
  description="A 34-year semiconductor engineer transforming into an AI Product Builder — the story of Chulbuji and Meta-Chulbuji"
>
  <div class="about-container">

    <h1 class="about-title">About: Chulbuji + Meta-Chulbuji</h1>
    <p class="about-lead">A human operating with AI — Chulbuji's AI Product Builder transformation record</p>

    <!-- 01 Identity -->
    <section class="about-section">
      <span class="section-label">01 — Identity</span>
      <h2 class="section-title">Chulbuji + Meta-Chulbuji: Dual Brain</h2>

      <p>chulbuji.com is the transformation record of a 34-year semiconductor process engineer — 'Chulbuji' — becoming an AI Product Builder. This is where AX (AI Transformation) gets executed and accumulated, not just declared.</p>

      <p>Instead of freezing before the tidal wave of technological change, I chose to embrace AI as a second brain. There is <strong>'Chulbuji'</strong> — the human mind that holds intent and direction. And there is <strong>'Meta-Chulbuji'</strong> — the AI mind that gives those thoughts structure and executes on them. This site chronicles the Dual-Brain collaboration between the two: unfiltered, in real time.</p>

      <blockquote class="philosophy-quote">
        Learning wider, exploring deeper, and building things today that yesterday's version of me couldn't have imagined. This is a space that trusts the process over the product, and the experiment over the polished outcome.
      </blockquote>

      <p>chulbuji.com is a personal project hub where real projects are built and operated alongside AI — and the execution records and decision criteria gained along the way are documented here. Auto-trading, an AI content service, the blog/AdSense experiment, and website operations improvements are recorded not as success stories, but as genuine trial-and-error and learning in real time.</p>
    </section>

    <!-- 02 Perspective -->
    <section class="about-section">
      <span class="section-label">02 — Perspective</span>
      <h2 class="section-title">AI doesn't hand you answers — it sharpens your questions</h2>

      <p>I don't think of AI as a faster search engine or an answer machine. To me, AI is a <strong>partner</strong> that stretches my thinking and gives shape to half-formed ideas — which is exactly why I call it meta-chulbuji.</p>

      <div class="perspective-cards">
        <div class="perspective-card">
          <h3 class="card-title">The evolution of inquiry</h3>
          <p>Conversations with AI change the questions I ask. 'How do I do this?' deepens into 'Why does this work this way?', and then into 'What new possibilities open up if I redesign this entirely?'</p>
        </div>
        <div class="perspective-card">
          <h3 class="card-title">The velocity of execution</h3>
          <p>Ideas that used to live only in my head now become rapid prototypes through AI collaboration. They don't need to be perfect. Some things only reveal themselves once you've built them.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="perspective-card">
          <h3 class="card-title">Experience as a lasting asset</h3>
          <p>Tools change. Technologies pass. But the insights I gain through the process stay with me. The real content of this site isn't how to use a tool — it's how using that tool changed <em>the person holding it</em>.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- 03 What You'll Find Here -->
    <section class="about-section">
      <span class="section-label">03 — What You'll Find Here</span>
      <h2 class="section-title">The Update Log</h2>

      <p>Three kinds of records accumulate here over time.</p>

      <div class="content-cards">
        <div class="content-card">
          <h3 class="content-card-name">Log</h3>
          <p class="content-card-sub">Raw Records</p>
          <p>Morning conversations with AI, the messy process of shaping ideas and putting them into motion. Unpolished snapshots of a mind at work.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="content-card">
          <h3 class="content-card-name">Projects</h3>
          <p class="content-card-sub">Things We Built</p>
          <p>Tools, services, and experiments brought to life through Dual-Brain collaboration. Small and imperfect, perhaps — but real, and made.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="content-card">
          <h3 class="content-card-name">Insights</h3>
          <p class="content-card-sub">Discoveries About Myself</p>
          <p>Shifts in thinking and fragments of self-understanding that emerged through AI interaction — things I never would have found thinking alone.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- 04 Goal -->
    <section class="about-section about-goal">
      <span class="section-label">04 — Goal</span>
      <h2 class="section-title">Transformation is not a declaration — it's accumulation.</h2>

      <p>My goal is not to stack up polished achievements. It is to execute AX through dual-brain and multi-expert AI orchestration, and to build that record openly. To remain a human who never stops <strong>self-updating</strong> in the uncharted territory of AI civilization.</p>

      <p>If you've found your way here while wrestling with similar questions, I hope these records offer a small spark. We can each grow at our own pace, in our own way.</p>

      <nav class="about-nav" aria-label="Page navigation">
        <a href="/en/log/" class="about-nav-btn">Browse the Log</a>
        <a href="/en/projects/" class="about-nav-btn">View Projects</a>
        <a href="/en/start/" class="about-nav-btn">Start Here</a>
      </nav>
    </section>

    <!-- 05 AI Usage Principles -->
    <section class="about-section">
      <span class="section-label">05 — AI Usage Principles</span>
      <h2 class="section-title">AI is a partner — not an autonomous author</h2>

      <p>Every piece of content on this site is planned by the human operator ('Chulbuji'), written in collaboration with AI, and reviewed and edited by the operator before publication. AI does not judge, decide, or publish content autonomously.</p>

      <div class="principle-list">
        <div class="principle-item">
          <strong>Review responsibility</strong>
          <p>The factual accuracy, appropriateness of expression, and correctness of information in all AI-generated content is verified by the operator. AI errors may result in inaccuracies — if you spot one, please reach out via <a href="/en/contact">Contact</a>.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="principle-item">
          <strong>Acknowledging limitations</strong>
          <p>AI is a powerful tool, but it can be wrong. Rather than following AI suggestions uncritically, the process of questioning, verifying, and sometimes rejecting them is part of what gets recorded here.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="principle-item">
          <strong>Transparent record-keeping</strong>
          <p>Errors, misjudgments, and revision histories from AI collaboration are not hidden — they're part of the record. Failures and corrections sit alongside successes as core content on this site.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- 06 Content & Monetization -->
    <section class="about-section">
      <span class="section-label">06 — Content & Monetization</span>
      <h2 class="section-title">On sensitive topics and monetization</h2>

      <p>This site includes content of an experimental nature — auto-trading records, monetization experiments, and similar topics. The following applies clearly.</p>

      <div class="principle-list">
        <div class="principle-item">
          <strong>Auto-trading content</strong>
          <p>All auto-trading records are personal technical validation experiments. They are not investment advice, profit guarantees, or specific stock recommendations. Past experimental results do not predict future performance. All investment decisions remain the sole responsibility of the reader.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="principle-item">
          <strong>Advertising and monetization</strong>
          <p>This site may display Google AdSense advertisements. Any ad revenue goes toward covering site operating costs. Ad placement does not influence editorial content or direction. All advertising complies with platform policies.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="principle-item">
          <strong>What readers can and cannot expect</strong>
          <p><strong>Can expect:</strong> genuine records of experiments and operations, honest trial-and-error, the operator's subjective judgment and reasoning.<br><strong>Cannot expect:</strong> guaranteed investment returns, expert-validated professional advice, specific stock recommendations.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about-container {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 2.5rem 1.25rem 4rem;
  }

  /* Page title */
  .about-title {
    font-size: clamp(1.625rem, 1.25rem + 1.875vw, 2.25rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    line-height: 1.25;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  }

  .about-lead {
    font-size: var(--font-size-lg);
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  /* Section structure */
  .about-section {
    padding-top: 2.75rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border-color);
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .section-label {
    display: block;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--primary-color);
    margin-bottom: 0.875rem;
  }

  .section-title {
    font-size: clamp(1.125rem, 1rem + 0.625vw, 1.375rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    line-height: 1.35;
    margin-bottom: 1.375rem;
    color: var(--text-color);
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }

  .about-section p {
    font-size: var(--font-size-base);
    line-height: 1.85;
    margin-bottom: 1.125rem;
    color: var(--text-color);
    max-width: 100%;
  }

  .about-section p:last-of-type {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  /* Philosophy quote */
  .philosophy-quote {
    border-left: 3px solid var(--primary-color);
    background: #f7f8ff;
    padding: 1.125rem 1.375rem;
    margin: 1.75rem 0 0;
    border-radius: 0 6px 6px 0;
    font-style: normal;
    color: #444;
    line-height: 1.85;
    font-size: var(--font-size-base);
  }

  /* Perspective cards */
  .perspective-cards {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 0.875rem;
    margin-top: 1.375rem;
  }

  .perspective-card {
    background: var(--background-alt);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 1.25rem 1.375rem;
  }

  .card-title {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--text-color);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }

  .perspective-card p {
    font-size: var(--font-size-base);
    color: #555;
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin-bottom: 0 !important;
  }

  /* Content cards (Log / Projects / Insights) */
  .content-cards {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 0.875rem;
    margin-top: 1.375rem;
  }

  .content-card {
    border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 1.25rem 1.375rem;
  }

  .content-card-name {
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--text-color);
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }

  .content-card-sub {
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-weight: 500;
    margin-bottom: 0.625rem !important;
  }

  .content-card p:last-child {
    font-size: var(--font-size-base);
    color: #555;
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin-bottom: 0 !important;
  }

  /* Goal section */
  .about-goal {
    padding-top: 3rem;
  }

  /* Navigation buttons */
  .about-nav {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.625rem;
    margin-top: 2.25rem;
  }

  .about-nav-btn {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    padding: 0.5rem 1.125rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
    border-radius: 6px;
    font-size: var(--font-size-sm);
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--text-color);
    text-decoration: none;
    background: white;
    min-height: 44px;
    transition: border-color 0.2s, color 0.2s, background-color 0.2s;
  }

  .about-nav-btn:hover {
    border-color: var(--primary-color);
    color: var(--primary-color);
    background-color: #f7f8ff;
  }

  /* Principle list (sections 05–06) */
  .principle-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.875rem;
    margin-top: 1.25rem;
  }

  .principle-item {
    border-left: 3px solid var(--border-color);
    padding: 0.875rem 1.25rem;
    background: var(--background-alt);
    border-radius: 0 6px 6px 0;
  }

  .principle-item strong {
    display: block;
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--text-color);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .principle-item p {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: #555;
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin-bottom: 0 !important;
  }

  /* Desktop: 3-column cards */
  @media (min-width: 640px) {
    .perspective-cards {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    }

    .content-cards {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    }
  }

  /* Small mobile */
  @media (max-width: 480px) {
    .about-container {
      padding: 2rem 1rem 3rem;
    }

    .about-nav {
      flex-direction: column;
    }

    .about-nav-btn {
      justify-content: center;
    }
  }
</style>
